This morning before we headed out to basketball try outs Carter said can you cover me in prayer before I try out… y’all i turned around looking like what? I’m not going to lie I was so confused & shocked but I said YESS!… I went in my room and just took a second… because this week has just been hit after hit… punches to the gut but still I overcome every obstacle… I’ve been a prayer warrior… one thing for sure Carter notices everything.. we pretty much grew up together he’s seen everything… I owe him everything… after we prayed I said why did you want me to pray over you… he said because you’re the only one I can go to & I can trust you! Chileeeeeeeee you talking about tearsss… lately Carter had just been saying some real grown boy stuff and it’s like you’re 13 how do you even know what to say? I thought I failed him as a mom early and if you know me you know why…Listen your children are watching… I’ve been an overwhelmed mom but this week Ive been so DANG ON appreciative of me and mines…  I’m so grateful! Being a single Mom in a state where I have no family is hard at times but I know for sure we know we all we got! GRATITUDE!! 
#momlife #boymom #momof3

Happy Birthday to my baby Cree Rose 💙
9/18/19 #virgobaby
Mini Cake by @allthingsprettylit duhh

Cree is 3 weeks into Pre-K Exceptional Program and he lovesssss it! I was so nervous about him being at school and now I’m actually excited to put him in his uniform every morning! He gets so excited when his teachers comes to the door to get him in the morning! It just makes me feel at peace and provides so much security that he’s okay when he’s not with me! And he’s learning!!!!!! 🧩

Quick back ground story… I was selling plates and @_moniec_ bought one from me! She picked it up and told me how she’s been following my journey with Cree! She’s the principal at a CMS elementary school here in Charlotte and gave me so many resources to get Cree started in the Exceptional Pre-K Classroom! I’m so thankful for you! Thank you so much!! Black Girl Rocking it! 💙 

Parents who are new or going through this:… don’t be afraid to receive help… don’t be afraid to ask questions… this journey isn’t the easiest but I wouldn’t trade it for ANYTHING…. You’re strong… you’re powerful… you can do it!!! 😘

#autismprek #autismawareness #autistickids #autismmom #hesfournow

📌NO GATEKEEPING SAVE THIS REEL! 

There’s so many things that work for everyone else but what I’ve been finding that works as a hairstylist is…. 

1️⃣ CONSISTENCY- I fall off all the time… but as soon as I post 3 reels back to back AM, NOON, PM… I’m back on! 6-8am post put me back in the loop of being seen! 

2️⃣ 5 SECOND VIDEOS: looping videos…increases replays & watch time! The video will keep starting over… every time it starts over it’s a view! 

3️⃣ AUDIOS UNDER 8k reels usage: I like using audios that aren’t trending more than the ones that are trending. They aren’t over used and you won’t get lost in the content creation batch…When the audio does blow up you will be seen relatively first. 

4️⃣: PROVIDING REAL VALUE: Know what you’re talking about. Spark interest… PROVIDE FACTS! 

5️⃣ COMMENTS: get knee deep in the comments… respond and interact!! You might not be able to answer them all but respond when you can… ignore the negativity but let it sit there… opinions are opinions yet it boosts your engagement.
